	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Outstanding psychiatric reports have caused a delay in the case of a Mpumalanga woman, who is accused of murdering her four children. Zinhle Maditla, aged 24, appeared in the Witbank Magistrate's Court on Tuesday where the case was postponed to April 4. READ: Mother turns herself in after 4 children found dead and wrapped in blankets in home "I can confirm that the woman accused of murdering her four children appeared in the Witbank District Court today and her matter has been postponed to 4 April, 2019 for a psychiatric report," National Prosecuting Authority spokesperson Monica Nyuswa said. In January, Maditla handed herself over to the police after the bodies of the four children were discovered inside her house in Klarinet, Witbank, police said. She later abandoned her bid for bail and opted to have her mental condition evaluated instead, News24 reported in January. She remains in custody. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  WATCH: Rohde 'used wife's body as a show house' to sell his story – Judge Judge Gayaat Salie-Hlophe referenced Jason Rohde's history as the former CEO of Lew Geffen Sotheby's International Realty by comparing the staging of his wife's suicide to the staging of a house by estate agents. WATCH: Three accused of murdering Mihalik appear in court The three men accused of Pete Mihalik's murder - Vuyile Maliti, Sinozokohle Biyela and Nkosinathi Khumalo - appear in the Cape Town Magistrate's Court on Friday 15 February 2019.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.